<div type="translation" n="notyet">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>. . .  the Council and the People  . . .  decreed to honour  . . .  praise  . . .   and crown him   . . .  and to erect ] an image of bronze in the Agora and [another one painted] in the sanctuary of Ares, carrying this inscription: The People has honoured [?Pere]itas son of Adrastos, priest of Ares, a fine and good man, with praise, a golden crown, an image of bronze, another one painted, and a front seat at the contests, for his excellence and for his continual benevolence to the whole people: and to erect a marble stele in the sanctuary of Ares on [which] this decree shall be inscribed.</p>
</div>
